Fig. S2
).

Distribution
. Today, 

C. religiosa

is confined to the Upper Nile valley and delta (
Fig. 1
). Its current population status is unknown (

Hutterer 
et al.,
2008

; 
Happold, 2013
). The most recently reported collection dates from 1988 (
Handwerk, 1990
). A possible Pleistocene record from Bir Tarfawi indicates the species also may have occurred in southern Egypt at that time, but the identity of the fossil fragments needs to be confirmed (

Kowalski 
et al.,
1989

; 
Butler, 1998
).
